Allurra Diashiea (Dark Elf 51 Wizard)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukukjr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kukjr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 7:21:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magelo</span><hr size=1> Most people like to comment based on emotional viewpoints.  But if you boil down the race issue with warriors this is what you get:<br>
<br>
All warriors have same class abilities<br>
Ogres add additional benefits that are made for melee:<br>
1) Ability to slam (stun enemies while duel wielding)<br>
2) Immune to stun from the front.<br>
3) Very high starting Strength and Stamina - two most important stats to a melee class<br>
<br>
They have negatives:<br>
large race, awkward in dungeons<br>
evil race, limits access to some cities (freeport for example)<br>
<br>
When you get to the high end game, if thats your goal, the advantages of ogres so far outweigh the disadvantages, you forget about the disadvantages entirely.<br>
<br>
Note - Some like to point out that kick, past level 56 I believe, can stun.  However kick ability caps at 210 and slam ability caps at 240.  So which would you rather rely on to stun a gating mob or interrupt a caster?<br>
<br>
The large size is very easily overcome with shrink potions.  Or eventually if you play long enough, a cobalt bracer.  Or wolf form.  Or boon of the garou... Bottom line is that the negatives of ogres are very easily counteracted but the positives can't be made up for by other races.<br>
<br>
If you don't think that being stunned matters watch an evenly equipped ogre try to gain and hold agro on ubermobs and another race getting stunned.  Anyone being objective and watching from a neutral perspective will see that because the ogre doesn't get stunned, and therefore does more constant and uninterrupted damage, will gain and hold agro better.<br>
<br>
I'm not knocking people playing whatever race they want.  It's a game, play what you have the most fun with.  But if you want to play the best warrior you can in terms of doing the things warriors do well, there is absolutely no substitute for ogre.  And no one can debate that from a logical view.   <p>Kukjr<BR>
54th Ogre Warrior<BR>
<BR>
formerly<BR>
Kukgrol Krusha<BR>
Ogre Warlord<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujareckthundershot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jareck Thundershot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/02 9:03:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magelo</span><hr size=1> If you were going for hp/stam, wouldn't SS be the better choice as opposed to Kael, assuming with other gear you can still hit the ac soft cap? <p><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/electronic/Everquestakirotag/JAROUTTAG.html">

